##
## Reconnaissance des formats/Wanton
##
@NODE reco_wanton "* Format Wanton *"

 ******************************************************************
 * ----------- Heading model for << Wanton Packer >> ------------ *
 * -------------------------------------------------------------- *
 * ------ Provenance : FINLANDIA Music-disk "Lucid Dreams" ------ *
 ******************************************************************

 Same as Protracker till this address :

 In - mod+$438 - there is no "M.K." but "WN" + 00 + a byte standing for
 the number of used patterns.

 Then, the patterns are packed like this :

 example in $43c, the longword 14 08 0C 00 :
                                |  |  |  |
                             note  |  |  value 00 (thus Volume = 00)
                                   |  | 
                              sample  effect (here Volume)

 430: 00000000 00000000 574E0015 14080C00    ........WN......     
 440: 00000F06 2C040C01 14050C00 00000EA1    ....,..........ˇ     
 450: 00000000 00000000 00000EA1 00000EA1    ...........ˇ...ˇ     
 460: 3A040C02 00000000 00000EA2 00000EA1    :..........˘...ˇ     
 470: 00000000 00000000 00000EA1 00000EA1    ...........ˇ...ˇ     
@ENDNODE

##
## Reconnaissance des formats/UNIC
##
@NODE reco_UNIC "* Format UNIC Tracker *"

 ******************************************************************
 * ----------- Heading model for << UNIC Tracker >> ------------- *
 * -------------------------------------------------------------- *
 * ---- Provenance : SLL's tune in KEFRENS "Egregious" Demo ----- *
 ******************************************************************

 The UNIC format is very similar to Protracker...

 At least in the heading... same length : 1084 bytes.
 Even the "M.K." is present, sometimes !!

 Maybe to disturb the rippers.. hehe but Pro-Wizard doesn't test this only!


