##
## Reconnaissance des formats/Power Music
##
@NODE reco_PowerMusic "* Format Power Music *"



This format is created by the tool "OPTIMOD" (by Joakim Ögren).

Very similar to a PTK mod, except that the $7F becomes $FF and when you
select the "NEWPM" option, the "M.K." becomes "!PM!".

The patterns are not changed...

But the samples are (with NEWPM option).

It's a kind of "Delta Packing" to make them more packable...

@ENDNODE



##
## Reconnaissance des formats/STP3
##
@NODE reco_STP3 "* Format Soundtracker Pro 3.0 *"

******************************************************************
* -------- Heading model for << Soundtracker Pro 3.0 >> -------- *
* -------------------------------------------------------------- *
* --------------- Provenance : STP3.Gyroscope ------------------ *
******************************************************************


I've  discovered this format thanks to Ronny PASSENHEIM (Yoho!)
who sent me 2 modules of this kind...

If anybody owns the tool itself, I'd like to see it ! Thanx


I think it's more like a STK-15 packer, than a PTK-31 ;)


Indeed, there are some "D10" effects which are in fact : "A01" (volslide \/)
As in some old STK-15 modules...


The "1" & "2" effects seem to be bad too.... strange...too fast !

That's why I'd like to see the original tool ! To check it...


