##
## Reconnaissance des formats/Hornet
##
@NODE reco_HRT "* Format Hornet Packer *"

******************************************************************
* ---------- Heading model for : << Hornet Packer >> ----------- *
* -------------------------------------------------------------- *
* --------------- Provenance : Alcatraz "Ilyad" ---------------- *
******************************************************************


Well, this format will not be found if you extract the modules
directly from the demo-files, there, they will be in Protracker format.
(As the Polka Packer)

But, if you try to rip the tunes after running the demo, thus, in memory,
you will find this format, a ProRunner-like format...

In the header, you will find the absolute addresses of the samples in memory
as they were when running the demo.

Here, I must thank "LOL" for sending me this format ! (Helloooo!)

Indeed, I have never tried to rip these tunes in memory !!
You just have to extract the Protracker-tunes from the bigfiles composing
the "Ilyad" demo ! There are tons of XPK'ed files, joined together...


But, for those who're used to rip in memory, here is the format :


